-- Toshiba plans to bid for Areva T&D unit: sources
-- 
-- Fri Sep 4, 2009 1:40am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/09/04/us-areva-bid-idUSTRE58311X20090904

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Japan's Toshiba Corp ( 6502.T ) plans to bid for French nuclear group Areva's CEPFi.PA power distribution and transmission unit in a deal that could cost it more than 500 billion yen ($5.4 billion), sources said on Friday. 

 ($1=92.56 Yen) (Reporting by  Taiga Uranaka , Reiji Murai, Kentaro Hamada)